  "generated_pr_body": "## PURPOSE\nPB-044 simulates the PB-043 GitHub App onboarding plan to verify that each phase is executable under USBAY fail-closed governance before any live GitHub action occurs.\n\n## RISK\nIf onboarding phases lack evidence, approvals, fail-closed conditions, or audit outputs, USBAY could begin GitHub connector onboarding without sufficient control over credential authority, mutation approval, auditability, or rollback.\n\n## POLICY LINK\nAGENTS.md fail-closed, audit-first engineering, human oversight, branch governance, network governance, and secret/data hygiene rules. PB-043 GitHub Connector Onboarding Plan.\n\n## REQUIRED APPROVALS\nUSBAY-AUDIT and USBAY-GLOBAL23 review are required before merge. This PB does not authorize GitHub App creation, credential creation, API calls, repository mutation, or production activation.\n\n## GOVERNANCE CHECKS\nJSON evidence must parse. Simulation must verify all PB-043 phases define required evidence, approvals, fail-closed conditions, audit outputs, and completion criteria. Diff hygiene, conflict marker scan, metadata validation, and required governance section checks must pass.\n\n## AUDIT\nPB-044 generates governance/evidence/pb044/github_onboarding_readiness_execution.json with per-phase simulation results, missing artifact analysis, onboarding safety answer, required controls, and evidence requirements.\n\n## IMPACT\nUSBAY can begin governed onboarding preparation only because the plan is executable in simulation. Live GitHub mutation remains blocked until each phase produces real evidence and human review approves progression.\n\n## Decision\nVERIFIED\n\n## Status\nREADY_FOR_REVIEW\n",
